The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has announced the confirmation of 20 new cases of Covid-19 .
NCDC also announced that the country recorded two deaths in Lagos and Edo States.
, “Twenty new cases of COVID-19 have been reported in Nigeria; 11 in Lagos, three in the FCT, three in Edo, 2 in Osun and one in Ondo.
“Two new deaths have been recorded in Lagos and Edo States.
“As of 10:30 pm on 3rd of April, there are 210 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria.
Lagos still leads with 109 cases while Abuja and Osun follow in that order.
Ondo has got a case too, The virus now has spread across the whole of southwest.

			
